  "prompt": "What's a good moveset for Rockruff in Pokemon Sun and Moon?",
  "response": "In Pok\u00e9mon Sun and Moon, Rockruff is a Rock-type Pok\u00e9mon that can take advantage of its speed and attack power. Here's a good moveset that you can consider:\n\n### Rockruff Moveset\n\n**Ability:** Keen Eye / Vital Spirit (for Rockruff\u2019s evolution, Lycanroc, the ability changes depending on the form)\n\n**Nature:** Jolly (+Speed, -Special Attack) or Adamant (+Attack, -Special Attack)\n\n**EV Spread:** 252 Attack / 252 Speed / 4 HP\n\n#### Suggested Moves:\n\n1. **Stone Edge** \n   - A strong STAB (Same Type Attack Bonus) move with high power and a chance to critically hit. It\u2019s Rockruff's primary attacking move.\n\n2. **Close Combat**\n   - Provides coverage against Rock-types and Steel-types that threaten Rockruff. High damage, but comes with a defensive trade-off.\n\n3. **Swords Dance**\n   - Useful for boosting Rockruff's Attack to make its physical moves even more potent. Set up on switches or against tanky Pok\u00e9mon.\n\n4. **Accelerock**\n   - A priority move that allows Rockruff to outspeed and finish off weakened opponents. Great for picking off foes that are low on health.\n\n### Alternative Moves:\n\n- **Crunch**: Good coverage against Ghost-types and Psychic-types.\n- **Rock Slide**: Lower power than Stone Edge but has the advantage of increased accuracy and a chance to flinch.\n- **Thunder Fang**: Coverage against Water- and Flying-types, and can also inflict paralysis.\n\n### Strategy:\n\n- Use **Swords Dance** to boost your Attack if you have the opportunity.\n- Utilize **Accelerock** to finish off weakened opponents or to gain priority in battles.\n- Ensure you maximize your damage output with **Stone Edge** and **Close Combat** when necessary.\n\n### Evolutions:\n\nKeep in mind Rockruff can evolve into different forms of Lycanroc depending on the time of day in-game (Midday form during the day, Midnight form at night). Therefore, your final moveset might also depend on the form you choose post-evolution.\n\nThis moveset focuses on taking advantage of Rockruff\u2019s speed and offensive capabilities, making it a formidable attacker in battles. Enjoy training your Rockruff!",
